docker compose down client-app
docker compose build --no-cache client-app
docker compose up -d client-app

#All in one
docker compose down && docker compose build --no-cache client-app && docker compose up -d --build
docker compose down && docker compose up -d --build









â— For the clean rebuild without cache, I used:

  docker compose build --no-cache [service-name]

  To build all services without cache in a single command, you can use:

  docker compose build --no-cache

  This will rebuild all services defined in your docker-compose.yml without using any cache.

  If you want to force a complete rebuild including pulling fresh base images, you can combine it with the --pull flag:

  docker compose build --no-cache --pull

  For an even more thorough clean rebuild, you can use this sequence:

  # Remove all containers, networks, and volumes
  docker compose down -v --remove-orphans

  # Remove all images (optional - only if you want to rebuild from scratch)
  docker rmi $(docker images -f "dangling=true" -q) 2>/dev/null || true
  docker system prune -af

  # Build everything fresh without cache
  docker compose build --no-cache --pull

  # Start all services
  docker compose up -d

  Or as a single comprehensive command:

  docker compose down -v --remove-orphans && docker system prune -af && docker compose build --no-cache --pull && docker compose up -d

  This will:
  1. Stop and remove all containers, networks, and volumes
  2. Clean up all unused Docker resources
  3. Rebuild all images without cache and pull fresh base images
  4. Start all services

